@Linus Crew: Regarding @10:30 : I do. I want this. 

The ability to lock my FPS at 120 and run FMF to double that to 240 for my 240hz monitor has been my favorite new feature added to either GPU brand in years (and I'm very excited that NVIDIA has this scheduled to come out soon for the 40 series cards so I can compare with my partner's GPU). Unlike 60 vs 120 input latency, the feel of 120 vs true 240 input latency is much, much less noticeable and the FMF smoothing has been a god send for still hitting my refresh rate cap at 1440p in this modern era of games shooting for seemingly 60FPS performance before framegen without having to set everything in games to the absolute bare minimum settings. I have also found that FMF2 has way, way more stable frames in certain games such as MHWilds and Darktide, where turning on FSR3.1FG just murders my FPS. Even more importantly, I CAN TURN ON FMF WHILE USING XESS TO GET AROUND THE HORRIFIC PIXELATED MESS THAT IS FSR3. Though, if the rumors are true and FSR4 is coming to 7000 cards later, I'm excited to compare in person without the horrific youtube compression.

Also, regarding FMF2.1. I don't know why it seems to be different in your examples, but in both Path of Exile and Darktide, my most recent games I've been playing, there was a noticeable removal of ghosting in my Steam Overlay FPS, which used to look like it was performing tiny Alucard backdashes all over the corner of my screen and now, when observing casually as it didn't bother me in the first place, I haven't actually seen an example of that happening.

